{"id":"adore","term":"Adore","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>To worship; to express reverence and homage. The forms of adoration among the Jews were putting off the shoes (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 3:5\">Ex. 3:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 5:15\">Josh. 5:15</a>), and prostration (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 17:3\">Gen. 17:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 95:6\">Ps. 95:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 44:15\">Isa. 44:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 44:17\">17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:19\">19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 46:6\">46:6</a>). To “kiss the Son” in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 2:12\">Ps. 2:12</a> is to adore and worship him. (See <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 3:5\">Dan. 3:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 3:6\">6</a>.) The word itself does not occur in Scripture.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 3:5","Joshua 5:15","Genesis 17:3","Psalms 95:6","Isaiah 44:15","Isaiah 44:17","Genesis 1:19","Genesis 46:6","Psalms 2:12","Daniel 3:5","Daniel 3:6"]}